A couple's move to a new house turned into tragedy after their nine-year-old son drowned in the pool at the complex in Sunnyside. JOHANNESBURG A nine-year-old boy has drowned in a pool at a complex in Sunnyside Pretoria.The boy s parents had just moved into the complex.The boy allegedly took a stroll around the complex yesterday but did not return home.Netcare 911 spokesperson Chris Botha says the parents filed a missing person's report after searching the area with no luck. Botha says neighbours raised the alarm when they spotted the nine-year-old in the pool. The paramedics pulled the boy out of the pool and declared him dead at the scene. 